      "side": 1,
      "message": "Second that. I\u0027d prefer to have a separate function with a different semantic, e.g. \u0027SetExitingMode()\u0027, which just notifies the crash service that emulator\u0027s exiting. If we detect a crash after this function call, we treat it as a crash on exit and do whatever we need.\nThis way it\u0027s more incapsulated, so we can easily change the implementation later.\nNow I\u0027d suggest to create a separate file in the data exchange directory which would also contain some data about the exiting process, e.g. timestamp, how user initiated exit etc",
